# ============================================================
# Root .env.example
# This file is for documentation ONLY.
# Do NOT use this as a real env file for running the app.
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Backend API (app/api)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# In app/api/.env, you should have:
#
# PORT=5000
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/iniq
# JWT_SECRET=change-this-secret
# NODE_ENV=development
#
# Adjust values for production (Render/Railway + MongoDB Atlas).

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Frontend Web (app/web)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# In app/web/.env, you should have:
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
#
# For production, point this to your deployed API URL.

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Global notes
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# - Never commit real .env files with secrets.
# - Keep this .env.example updated so teammates know
#   what variables they need to set in app/api and app/web.
